&lt;h1 id="the-word-hacker"&gt;The Word &amp;ldquo;Hacker&amp;rdquo;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;April 2004&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To the popular press, &amp;ldquo;hacker&amp;rdquo; means someone who breaks into computers. Among programmers it means a good programmer. But the two meanings are connected. To programmers, &amp;ldquo;hacker&amp;rdquo; connotes mastery in the most literal sense: someone who can make a computer do what he wants—whether the computer wants to or not.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>